Week 1: AWS Fundamentals
- IAM (Identity and Access Management)
  - Creating and managing users, groups
  - Role-based access control
  - Security best practices
  - Policy creation and management
- VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)
  - Network design and architecture
  - Subnet configuration
  - Security groups and NACLs
  - Internet and NAT gateways

 Week 2: AWS Compute Services
- EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)
  - Instance types and families
  - AMI creation and management
  - Launch templates
  - Auto Scaling groups
- ECS (Elastic Container Service)
  - Task definitions
  - Service creation
  - Cluster management
  - Container instances

 Week 3: Storage and Database Services
- S3 (Simple Storage Service)
  - Bucket creation and management
  - Storage classes
  - Versioning and lifecycle policies
  - Access control
- AWS Database Services
  - RDS setup and management
  - DynamoDB basics
  - Backup and recovery
  - Performance optimization

 Week 4: AWS Developer Tools
- CodeCommit
  - Repository setup
  - Git workflows
  - Branch management
  - Security and access
- CodeBuild
  - Build projects
  - buildspec.yml configuration
  - Custom build environments
  - Build caching

 Week 5: Continuous Integration/Deployment
- CodePipeline
  - Pipeline creation
  - Stage configuration
  - Integration with other AWS services
  - Automated releases
- CodeDeploy
  - Application deployment
  - Deployment strategies
  - Rolling updates
  - Blue-green deployments

 Week 6: Container Services Deep Dive
- ECR (Elastic Container Registry)
  - Repository management
  - Image pushing and pulling
  - Image scanning
  - Access control
- EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)
  - Cluster setup
  - Node groups
  - Kubernetes integration
  - Service deployment

 Week 7: Infrastructure as Code
- CloudFormation
  - Template design
  - Stack creation and updates
  - Parameter management
  - Nested stacks
- AWS CDK
  - Infrastructure as code basics
  - Stack deployment
  - Resource creation
  - Best practices

 Week 8: Monitoring and Observability
- CloudWatch
  - Metrics and dashboards
  - Alarms configuration
  - Log management
  - Custom metrics
- AWS X-Ray
  - Distributed tracing
  - Service maps
  - Performance analysis
  - Troubleshooting

 Practical Assignments for Each Week:
1. Set up a secure AWS environment with proper IAM configurations
2. Deploy and scale applications using EC2 and ECS
3. Implement storage solutions and database backups
4. Create and manage source code repositories
5. Build CI/CD pipelines for application deployment
6. Deploy containerized applications
7. Create infrastructure using CloudFormation
8. Set up monitoring and alerting for AWS resources
